709393f-a.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 24th Street (West)
709393f-a.text:
725-727 Sixth Avc., west side, south of, and adjoining the S.W. corner
of west 24th Street, showing (No. 725) the Sixth Ave. ''Playground''. It is
provided with a rifle range, many slot-machine games, and cheap recorded
wusic, as a diversion for people with not too fine an appreciation of good en-
tertainment. It is similar to many such places found in Coney Ialsnd.
December 24, 1936.
L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

709396f-b.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 24th Street (West)
709396f-b.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from West 24th Street. showing
a reclaimed thoroughfare. This has been brought about
by the recent demolition of the old 'El' structure that
formerly darkened this Avenue. In the left background
appears the Greeley Square section with it's distinctive
Hotel McAlpin. Dominoting the skyline is the towering
Empire State Building.
March 29, 1939
P. L. Sperr
NO RERODUCTIONS
(2)
The same area from a point slirhtly south of
24th Streot. Note the cleared site at the N.E. corner
of same. This is being used by subway contractors as
a storage base and tunnel entrance.
October 28, 1939
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
